{{Infobox person | name = Quentin Kenihan | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Quentin Kenihan | birth_date = {{Birth date|1975|02|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Box Hill, Victoria]], Australia | death_date = {{Death date and age|2018|10|06|1975|02|27|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]], Australia | nationality = Australian | other_names = | occupation = Disability advocate, actor | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = ''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]'' }}
'''Quentin Kenihan''' (27 February 1975 – 6 October 2018) was an Australian disability advocate, writer and actor. He was born with [[osteogenesis imperfecta]], a rare bone disease.<ref name="SMH">{{cite news |last1=Miller |first1=Benjamin |title=Disability advocate Quentin Kenihan dies |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/disability-advocate-quentin-kenihan-dies-20181007-p50892.html |accessdate=7 October 2018 |work=Sydney Morning Herald |date=7 October 2018}}</ref>
Kenihan was born in [[Box Hill, Victoria]] in 1975 and first came to the attention of the public aged seven when he was the feature of a documentary by Australian journalist [[Mike Willesee]].<ref name="ABC">{{cite news |last1=Keane |first1=Daniel |title=Quentin Kenihan, disability advocate and actor, dies in Adelaide aged 43 |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-10-07/disability-advocate-quentin-kenihan-dies-in-adelaide-aged-43/10348452 |accessdate=7 October 2018 |work=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |date=7 October 2018}}</ref> He later was the host of a [[Ten Network]] television show ''Quentin Crashes''.<ref name="TenDaily">{{cite news |last1=Clark |first1=Georgia |title=Disability Advocate Quentin Kenihan Has Died, Aged 43 |url=https://tendaily.com.au/news/a181007gsj/disability-advocate-quentin-kenihan-has-died-aged-43-20181007 |accessdate=7 October 2018 |work=Ten Daily |publisher=Network Ten |date=7 October 2018}}</ref> In 2016, Kenihan participated in a lengthy television interview with [[Ray Martin (television presenter)|Ray Martin]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Martin |first1=Ray |title=Quentin Kenihan Uncensored |url=https://www.9now.com.au/a-current-affair/2016/extras/latest/160923/quentin-kenihan-uncensored |publisher=[[A Current Affair (Australian TV program)|A Current Affair]] |accessdate=7 October 2018 |date=2016}}</ref>
He appeared in the 2015 film ''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]'' in the role of Corpus Colossus.<ref name="ABC" /> Kenihan died in Adelaide on 6 October 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/oct/07/quentin-kenihan-australian-author-actor-and-disability-advocate-dies|title=Quentin Kenihan: Australian author, actor and disability advocate dies|last=Press|first=Australian Associated|date=2018-10-07|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-10-07|publisher=Australian Associated Press}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-10-07/disability-advocate-quentin-kenihan-dies-in-adelaide-aged-43/10348452|title=Disability advocate Quentin Kenihan dies in Adelaide, aged 43|date=2018-10-07|work=ABC News|access-date=2018-10-07|language=en-AU}}</ref> His suspected cause of death was an asthma attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.9news.com.au/2018/10/07/14/31/adelaide-actor-and-disability-advocate-quentin-kenihan-has-died|title=Quentin Kenihan: Adelaide actor and disability advocate dies|website=www.9news.com.au|accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref> He had nominated to stand as a councillor for the [[City of Adelaide]] at the elections on 9 November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lga.sa.gov.au/page.aspx?c=82087|title=KENIHAN, Quentin|date=7 October 2018|publisher=Local Government Association of South Australia|accessdate=8 October 2018|via=www.lga.sa.gov.au}}</ref>
